---
name: xlsx
description: Create, read, and manipulate Excel spreadsheets (.xlsx, .xls, .csv) using the xlsx (SheetJS) and ExcelJS npm packages. Covers cells, formulas, charts, formatting, multiple sheets, data import/export, and pivot tables.
user-invocable: false
---

# xlsx Skill — Excel Spreadsheet Creation & Manipulation

This skill covers two complementary libraries for working with Excel files in Node.js:

1. **SheetJS (`xlsx`)** — fastest reader/writer, broad format support (xlsx, xls, csv, ods, etc.)
2. **ExcelJS (`exceljs`)** — rich formatting, charts, images, streaming

## Installation

```bash
npm install xlsx            # SheetJS
npm install exceljs         # ExcelJS (richer formatting/charts)
```

---

## SheetJS — Quick Start

```js
const XLSX = require('xlsx');

// --- READING ---
const workbook = XLSX.readFile('data.xlsx');
const sheetName = workbook.SheetNames[0];
const sheet = workbook.Sheets[sheetName];

// To array of arrays
const aoa = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_aoa(sheet);

// To array of objects (row 1 = headers)
const json = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_json(sheet);

// --- WRITING ---
const wb = XLSX.utils.book_new();
const data = [
  ['Name', 'Age', 'Score'],
  ['Alice', 30, 95],
  ['Bob',   25, 87],
];
const ws = XLSX.utils.aoa_to_sheet(data);
XLSX.utils.book_append_sheet(wb, ws, 'Results');
XLSX.writeFile(wb, 'output.xlsx');
```

---

## SheetJS — Detailed API

### Reading Files

```js
// From file path
const wb = XLSX.readFile('file.xlsx');

// From Buffer
const buf = fs.readFileSync('file.xlsx');
const wb = XLSX.read(buf, { type: 'buffer' });

// From base64 string
const wb = XLSX.read(b64string, { type: 'base64' });

// From URL (with node-fetch)
const resp = await fetch(url);
const ab = await resp.arrayBuffer();
const wb = XLSX.read(ab, { type: 'array' });

// Options
XLSX.readFile('file.xlsx', {
  cellDates: true,   // parse dates as Date objects
  cellNF: true,      // include number format strings
  sheetRows: 100,    // only read first 100 rows
  password: 'abc',   // password-protected files
});
```

### Sheet Ranges & Cells

```js
const ws = wb.Sheets['Sheet1'];

// Get sheet range
const range = XLSX.utils.decode_range(ws['!ref']);
// range = { s: {r:0, c:0}, e: {r:99, c:9} }

// Access a cell directly
const cellA1 = ws['A1'];
console.log(cellA1.v);  // raw value
console.log(cellA1.t);  // type: 'n'=number, 's'=string, 'b'=boolean, 'd'=date

// Iterate all cells
for (let row = range.s.r; row <= range.e.r; row++) {
  for (let col = range.s.c; col <= range.e.c; col++) {
    const addr = XLSX.utils.encode_cell({ r: row, c: col });
    const cell = ws[addr];
    if (cell) console.log(addr, cell.v);
  }
}

// Set a cell value
ws['B2'] = { t: 'n', v: 42 };
ws['C2'] = { t: 's', v: 'Hello' };
ws['D2'] = { t: 'f', f: 'A2+B2' };  // formula
```

### JSON <-> Sheet Conversion

```js
// Array-of-arrays to sheet
const ws = XLSX.utils.aoa_to_sheet([
  ['ID', 'Name', 'Value'],
  [1, 'Alpha', 100],
  [2, 'Beta',  200],
]);

// JSON (array of objects) to sheet
const ws = XLSX.utils.json_to_sheet([
  { ID: 1, Name: 'Alpha', Value: 100 },
  { ID: 2, Name: 'Beta',  Value: 200 },
]);

// Sheet to JSON
const rows = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_json(ws);
// [{ ID:1, Name:'Alpha', Value:100 }, ...]

// Sheet to CSV
const csv = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_csv(ws);

// Sheet to HTML table
const html = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_html(ws);
```

### Column Widths

```js
ws['!cols'] = [
  { wch: 10 },   // col A width 10 chars
  { wch: 25 },   // col B width 25 chars
  { wch: 15 },
];
```

### Row Heights

```js
ws['!rows'] = [
  { hpx: 30 },  // row 1 height in pixels
  { hpx: 20 },
];
```

### Merging Cells

```js
ws['!merges'] = [
  { s: { r: 0, c: 0 }, e: { r: 0, c: 3 } },  // A1:D1
  { s: { r: 5, c: 0 }, e: { r: 7, c: 0 } },  // A6:A8
];
```

### Writing Options

```js
XLSX.writeFile(wb, 'output.xlsx');
XLSX.writeFile(wb, 'output.xlsb', { bookType: 'xlsb', compression: true });
XLSX.writeFile(wb, 'output.csv',  { bookType: 'csv' });
XLSX.writeFile(wb, 'output.ods',  { bookType: 'ods' });

// To buffer
const buf = XLSX.write(wb, { type: 'buffer', bookType: 'xlsx' });

// To base64
const b64 = XLSX.write(wb, { type: 'base64', bookType: 'xlsx' });
```

